<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:13PM MDT  by NWS Aberdeen</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Clark
and east central Spink Counties through 600 PM CDT...
At 513 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Raymond, or 12 miles northwest of Clark, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of west central Clark
and east central Spink Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
